/* top */ Redundant. The title of the album and the artist are in the first sentence. That's all that is needed. "Eponymous" means "named for". It's unnecessary to say "Lil Pump is an album named for Lil Pump by Lil Pump". The word has been copied hundreds of times from other album articles without any consideration for what the word actually means.
/* Marriage and relationships */ The wedding wasn't held in Loomis (which wasn't called Placer since 1862) but in Auburn. Both places are located in Placer County, though.
